Delivery of the Special Examination

In 2025, VIA Rail continued to advance the Office of the Auditor General of Canada’s (OAG) Special Examination initiated in 2024, supporting the OAG’s independent work through sustained collaboration, structured evidence gathering, and timely engagement with management
and the Board. This in-depth review, conducted under the Financial Administration Act, underscores the Corporation’s commitment to transparency and accountability, with the Special Examination expected to be completed as part
of the OAG’s 2025–26 work plan.

Compensation

Director compensation at VIA Rail is determined by Order in Council. Both the Chairperson and other independent directors are compensated with an annual retainer for their service and participation in Committee and Board meetings. They also receive a fixed per diem for travel time. The compensation structure, which aligns with
the Treasury Board Guidelines, as follows:
  Chair of the Board: Receives an annual retainer of
$12,400 and a per diem of $485.
  Directors: Receive an annual retainer of $6,200 and the same per diem of $485.
  Chairs of Committees: Receive the base retainer plus an additional annual retainer of $6,200.
Directors are also reimbursed for reasonable out-of-pocket expenses incurred while performing their duties. These expenses include travel, accommodation, and meals.
Each Board member serves on multiple committees.

