Board and Management Training

In 2025, the Board of Directors continued to strengthen its effectiveness through a focused program of education sessions designed to deepen directors’ understanding
of VIA Rail’s operating environment, shareholder context, and enterprise risks. The Board engaged in briefings
on the macroeconomic outlook in Canada and globally to better assess key assumptions, demand and
cost pressures, and scenario impacts on planning and performance.
Directors also received updates on Transport Canada’s priorities, strengthening alignment with government expectations and enhancing the Board’s oversight
of strategic positioning and stakeholder engagement. The Board participated in an education session with the Canadian Armed Forces to enhance awareness of
security, resilience, and emergency response coordination, supporting stronger governance of business continuity and crisis preparedness.
Directors further explored maritime tourism and regional economic development perspectives to inform oversight of service opportunities, partnerships, and VIA Rail’s contribution to regional growth. Finally, the Board examined environmental sustainability and emergency preparedness to integrate climate and resilience considerations into its oversight of risk management, operational readiness, and long-term stewardship.

